100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 16, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament and international security amidst growing tensions in Europe. In the United States, debates intensified over the controversial Scopes Trial, highlighting the clash between science and religion in education. Meanwhile, in the Soviet Union, preparations for the upcoming Communist Party Congress signaled an ongoing consolidation of power under Joseph Stalin.
